name: Cucumber Dip
description: The dill flavor in this creamy summer favorite goes great with cucumber slices. Kids love it -- it never lasts long! Try this dip with other veggies, as well.
ingredients: 1 cup sour cream #1 cup mayonnaise #1 tablespoon dried minced onion #2 tablespoons dried parsley #2 teaspoons dried dill weed #2 teaspoons Beau Monde ™ seasoning #¼ teaspoon seasoning salt #⅛ teaspoon ground black pepper

name: Simple Cheese Straws
description: This is a great snack anytime. The kids just love them.
ingredients: 1 (8 ounce) package shredded Cheddar cheese #½ cup butter, softened #1 cup all-purpose flour #¼ teaspoon salt

name: Russian Creme Fruit Topping
description: A quick and tasty topping for fresh berries. May be served with a sugar wafer as garnish.
ingredients: 2 cups sour cream #¾ cup white sugar #1 teaspoon vanilla extract

name: Cheesy Chili Dip I
description: This is one of my family's favorite hot dips. It contains cubed cheese, chili, cream of mushroom soup, ground pork, and diced tomatoes with green chile peppers (e.g. Rotel).
ingredients: ½ pound finely chopped pork #16 ounces processed cheese food, cubed #1 (10 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chile peppers, drained #1 cup condensed cream of mushroom soup #1 (15 ounce) can chili #1 (14.5 ounce) package tortilla chips

name: Corned Beef on Toast
description: This creamy corned beef recipe is easily transformed into a delicious appetizer when served on toast triangles or used as a dip for bread sticks and cheeses. The amount of beef may be doubled.
ingredients: 2 tablespoons butter #2 tablespoons all-purpose flour #¼ tablespoon salt #1 ½ cups milk #8 ounces corned beef

name: Cheese Onion Garlic Bread
description: This is a great appetizer or side dish for your next get together.
ingredients: 2 French baguettes, cut into 3/4 inch diagonal slices #1 large minced onion #8 cloves minced garlic #¼ cup butter #2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese #½ cup grated Parmesan cheese #1 cup mayonnaise

name: Chicken a la King III
description: Easy and delicious, this a la King is a family favorite. Great for luncheons and buffets for the holidays.
ingredients: 2 tablespoons butter #1 green bell pepper, chopped #1 cup sliced fresh mushrooms #1 cup chicken broth #2 tablespoons all-purpose flour #2 ¼ cups cooked, cubed chicken breast meat #1 cup sour cream #2 egg yolks #1 pimento, chopped #4 teaspoons cooking sherry # salt and pepper to taste

name: Leftover Oven Barbequed Chicken
description: Leftover fried chicken baked with a vinegar, ketchup and water mixture. Easy, tangy, tasty. The chicken comes out tender and delicious, and the sauce is really good. My children have always enjoyed this dish!
ingredients: 2 ½ pounds leftover fried chicken legs #1 cup water #1 cup ketchup #½ cup apple cider vinegar # salt and pepper to taste

name: Super Simple Oven Barbequed Chicken
description: This dish is a good alternative to BBQ chicken and is also good for anyone on a carbohydrate restrictive diet. Lots if good flavor! This recipe can be altered to serve as little or as many as you like.
ingredients: 6 bone-in chicken breast halves, with skin #1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce #1 tablespoon hickory-flavored liquid smoke #2 teaspoons chili powder #2 teaspoons ground cumin #2 teaspoons garlic powder #2 teaspoons dried thyme #2 teaspoons dried oregano # salt and pepper to taste

name: Chicken, Stuffing and Green Bean Casserole
description: This is my family's favorite recipe. My mom gave it to me and it's terrific!
ingredients: 2 cups cooked, cubed chicken breast meat #1 (10.75 ounce) can condensed cream of chicken soup #1 (14.5 ounce) can green beans, drained # salt and pepper to taste #1 (12 ounce) package unseasoned dry bread stuffing mix #1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese

name: Apple Banana Smoothie
description: Thick and healthy fruit drink with apple, banana and orange juice. The frozen banana takes the place of shaved ice and results in a smooth, creamy texture. Serve with dollop of whipped cream for added effect.
ingredients: 1 frozen bananas, peeled and chopped #½ cup orange juice #1 Gala apple, peeled, cored and chopped #¼ cup milk

name: Maria's Stuffed Chicken Breasts
description: This is a great and easy chicken dish with a twist. How do you cook some chicken like Maria?! Like this!
ingredients: 4 skinless, boneless chicken breast halves # salt and pepper to taste #1 (15 ounce) container ricotta cheese #1 (10 ounce) package frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained #1 clove garlic, minced #2 eggs, beaten #1 (8 ounce) package shredded mozzarella cheese, divided #1 (16 ounce) jar spaghetti sauce

name: Mango Topping
description: Very rich in flavor. Good with ice cream.
ingredients: 3 cups mangos, peeled, seeded and chopped #1 tablespoon butter #1 tablespoon brown sugar #1 teaspoon lemon juice #1 teaspoon orange juice #3 tablespoons water

name: Beverage Cubes
description: Everyone has a favorite drink that is always in the fridge...but don't you hate it when your ice cubes melt and make your drink watery? Here's a simple solution! Use your favorite non-carbonated beverage; fruit juice, coffee and prepared drink mix all work great.
ingredients: 2 cups brewed black tea, cold

name: Cedarwood
description: A cool summer punch with cranberry juice, vodka and ginger ale over ice.
ingredients: 1 fluid ounce lemon juice #2 fluid ounces vodka #4 fluid ounces cranberry juice #3 ½ fluid ounces ginger ale

name: Clam Dip
description: This is an easy-to-make warm clam dip served with crackers.
ingredients: 3 (6.5 ounce) cans minced clams #2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice #¼ cup chopped onion #½ cup butter #1 pinch ground black pepper #1 cup dry bread crumbs #1 (8 ounce) package shredded sharp Cheddar cheese

name: Diva Colada
description: Pineapple juice, coconut cream and pineapple sherbet garnished with a fresh pineapple wedge and a cherry - this is a favorite of kids...
ingredients: 1 cup pineapple juice #2 cups pineapple sorbet #2 tablespoons cream of coconut #1 slice fresh pineapple #2 maraschino cherries

name: The Best Steak Sauce
description: Can hardly tell the difference between this and store bought.
ingredients: ½ cup raisins #⅔ cup ketchup #1 teaspoon chili powder #1 teaspoon seasoning salt #½ cup applesauce #2 tablespoons Italian-style salad dressing

name: Steak Fingers
description: Easy to make and a favorite of my family. Excellent with french fries and a salad!!
ingredients: ⅓ cup vegetable oil #1 pound round steak #2 eggs #½ cup milk # salt and pepper to taste #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour for coating

name: Teriyaki Steak Marinade
description: Marinate your favorite steak in this before grilling.
ingredients: 1 cup soy sauce #1 ¼ cups water #½ cup brown sugar #1 pinch ground ginger #1 teaspoon minced garlic #¼ cup minced onion #¼ cup sherry

name: Electric Strawberry
description: A quick and easy sweet after dinner drink of butterscotch schnapps, milk and grenadine.
ingredients: 1 fluid ounce butterscotch schnapps #4 fluid ounces milk #1 dash grenadine syrup #1 strawberry

name: Cottage Meatloaf
description: Garnish with fresh herbs, if desired.
ingredients: 1 ½ pounds lean ground beef #½ cup ketchup #⅓ cup tomato juice #½ teaspoon salt #½ teaspoon ground black pepper #⅛ teaspoon crushed red pepper #2 eggs, beaten #¾ cup fresh bread crumbs #¼ cup diced onion #2 teaspoons prepared mustard #½ cup ketchup #1 teaspoon prepared mustard #4 teaspoons brown sugar

name: Fresh Lemonade
description: A summer classic, this lemonade is easy and refreshing too!
ingredients: 10 lemons #3 cups water #2 cups white sugar #4 cups crushed ice

name: Golden Rays of Peach Delight
description: Very fresh and tasty alcoholic drink with an peachy-orange twist! Watch out and be sure to sip slowly - not for the faint-hearted!!!
ingredients: 1 (1.5 fluid ounce) jigger gin #1 (1.5 fluid ounce) jigger triple sec liqueur #½ fluid ounce peach schnapps #2 fluid ounces orange juice #2 fluid ounces lemon-lime flavored carbonated beverage #1 dash grenadine syrup

name: Handsome Party Punch
description: Can't get more handsome than citrus carbonated orange juice limeade punch, with raspberry sherbet on top!
ingredients: 1 (6 ounce) can frozen orange juice concentrate #1 (6 ounce) can frozen lemonade concentrate #3 liters lemon-lime flavored carbonated beverage #1 quart raspberry sherbet

name: Iced Tea I
description: Like real iced tea, but do you hate boiling the water and then waiting for the tea to cool? Try making it with hot tap water.
ingredients: 8 tea bags #½ cup hot water #7 ½ cups cold water

name: Kool Ade Punch
description: Makes a delicious drink and you can also float ice cream or sherbet on top.
ingredients: 1 (4.6 ounce) package cherry flavored sweetened soft drink mix #1 (46 fluid ounce) can unsweetened pineapple juice #1 liter lemon-lime flavored carbonated beverage #1 (6 ounce) can frozen orange juice concentrate, thawed #1 (6 ounce) can frozen lemonade concentrate, thawed

name: Lady Joy
description: Lemon rum and blue curacao at the bottom of a flute of sparkling wine.
ingredients: ⅔ fluid ounce lemon rum #⅔ fluid ounce Blue Curacao #6 fluid ounces champagne #1 twist lemon zest, garnish

name: Margarita Made Easy
description: The quirkiest, yet quickest frozen margarita with a taste that's hard to beat!!!
ingredients: 1 (6 ounce) can frozen limeade concentrate #4 (1.5 fluid ounce) jiggers tequila #6 fluid ounces caffeinated citrus-flavored soda

name: Citrus Slush
description: Orange and lime are blended with ice in this refreshing summer drink.
ingredients: 1 orange, peeled and chopped #1 lime, peeled and chopped #12 cubes ice

name: Raspberry Refresher
description: My grandmother used to make this for us after working in the barn on a hot summer day. Try using strawberries too. Garnish with a slice of lemon and a sprig of mint.
ingredients: 1 liter carbonated water #1 pint raspberries

name: Sassy Sangria
description: This is a sassy red wine punch that has tropical fruit floating in it. May be served with ice if desired.
ingredients: 1 gallon dry red wine #½ cup white sugar #1 (46 fluid ounce) can pineapple juice #1 (8 ounce) can pineapple chunks #1 orange, sliced into rounds #1 lime, sliced into rounds

name: Very Fruity Rum Punch
description: A great rum punch I invented with some extra kick, It has been a hit at more than one party...
ingredients: 1 ½ cups rum #⅓ cup banana liqueur #1 dash grenadine syrup #1 (6 ounce) can frozen orange juice concentrate #1 (6 ounce) can frozen pineapple juice concentrate #1 orange, sliced into rounds #1 lime, sliced into rounds #1 lemon, sliced into rounds

name: Wedding Day Punch
description: A colorful punch that is not only great for weddings but wedding and baby showers also! I use this one a lot because it is tasty and simple to prepare, just read the instructions and you'll see what I mean. can be doubled easily!
ingredients: 3 (64 fluid ounce) bottles orange juice #3 (46 fluid ounce) cans pineapple juice #1 (.25 ounce) package unsweetened lemonade drink mix #1 teaspoon almond extract #1 cup white sugar #1 (46 fluid ounce) can fruit punch

name: Yummy Pink Punch
description: Great tasting! Made it at my wedding! Everyone loved it! Raspberry sherbet and cranberry or raspberry ginger ale make this one a keeper!
ingredients: 4 liters cranberry ginger ale #1 gallon raspberry sherbet

name: Pennsylvania Dutch Sour Cream Cabbage
description: One head fresh cabbage simmered with sour cream, sugar, vinegar, flour, salt, pepper and oil.
ingredients: 1 medium head cabbage, shredded #½ cup oil for frying #1 teaspoon salt #½ teaspoon ground black pepper #2 cups white sugar #2 tablespoons all-purpose flour #1 pint sour cream #2 cups distilled white vinegar

name: Three Bean Salad I
description: Three Bean Salad with extra kinds of beans and a zesty flavor!
ingredients: 1 (14.5 ounce) can green beans, drained #1 (14.5 ounce) can wax beans, drained #1 (15.25 ounce) can red kidney beans, drained #1 (15 ounce) can garbanzo beans, drained #1 (15 ounce) can black beans, drained #1 red onion, chopped #1 green bell pepper, chopped #¾ cup red wine vinegar #¾ cup white sugar #¾ cup vegetable oil #¾ teaspoon ground dry mustard #½ teaspoon dried tarragon #1 ½ teaspoons dried cilantro

name: Banana Meatloaf
description: A moist and flavorful version of meatloaf!
ingredients: 1 pound lean ground beef #1 cup fresh bread crumbs #1 tablespoon minced onion #¾ cup mashed banana #½ teaspoon salt #⅛ teaspoon ground black pepper #¼ teaspoon paprika #½ teaspoon ground mustard

name: Cheese Bread
description: A favorite of all. Almost a meal in itself, and oh so flavorful! The blend of Parmesan, mozzarella and Cheddar melts to perfection, creating a filling, delicious treat.
ingredients: 1 (1 pound) loaf French bread, sliced horizontally #4 tablespoons butter #½ cup mayonnaise #1 cup grated Parmesan cheese #4 ounces grated mozzarella cheese #4 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese #¼ teaspoon garlic salt

name: Delicious Apple Sauce
description: This apple sauce truly is delicious - my grandma makes it all the time!
ingredients: 2 apples - peeled, cored and shredded #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #¼ cup water #3 tablespoons brown sugar

name: Loosemeat Sandwiches II
description: Very simple. I grew up in Iowa and I always thought these originated there. Serve on warm seeded buns.
ingredients: 1 pound lean ground beef #1 (10.75 ounce) can condensed chicken gumbo soup

name: Spicy Pakistani Zucchini
description: I am from Pakistan, and this recipe is from the Pakistani kitchen. This dish is traditionally served with chapati, but you can serve it with boiled rice too.
ingredients: ¼ cup cooking oil #1 onion, thinly sliced #6 zucchini - peeled, seeded and cut into semicircles #½ teaspoon salt #2 cups water #2 teaspoons chili powder #½ teaspoon ground turmeric #½ teaspoon garlic powder #1 teaspoon ground coriander seed #3 whole cloves #7 whole peppercorns #4 tomatoes, chopped #2 tablespoons plain yogurt

name: Three Bean Salad II
description: This recipe is from the 1920's. It was my sister in law's great grandmother's. I have tried many, but keep coming back to this one. I hope you enjoy it as much as my family does!
ingredients: 1 ¼ cups white sugar #3 teaspoons cornstarch #½ teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon ground dry mustard #1 ¼ cups water #½ cup cider vinegar #1 (14.5 ounce) can green beans, drained #1 (14.5 ounce) can wax beans, drained #1 (15.25 ounce) can red kidney beans, drained #½ cup finely chopped onion #½ cup finely chopped green bell pepper

name: Cocktail Birthday Cake
description: Two types of bread, ham and salami are layered with a mustard butter and frosted with cream cheese, curry powder and almonds to create a fun, delicious "cake" that is cut up into little pieces and served cold. The curry powder may be omitted.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups butter, softened #1 ½ tablespoons prepared mustard #16 slices rye bread #½ pound boiled ham, thinly sliced #16 slices white bread #½ pound cooked ham, thinly sliced #½ pound salami, thinly sliced #1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, softened #1 ½ teaspoons curry powder #4 ½ ounces toasted almonds

name: Chutney Eggs
description: Here's a zesty variation on an old favorite that your guests will look forward to every time they visit. Bacon and chutney are the keys to these flavor packed eggs.
ingredients: 12 eggs #¼ cup chutney #6 slices bacon #3 tablespoons mayonnaise #1 tablespoon chopped almonds

name: Zucchini Cheese Garlic Appetizer
description: Wonderful little biscuits filled with cooked zucchini and cheese. Garlic and herbs round out the flavor nicely.
ingredients: 4 cups grated zucchini #1 ¾ cups biscuit baking mix #¾ cup grated Parmesan cheese #1 cup shredded sharp Cheddar cheese #4 eggs, beaten #½ cup vegetable oil #1 large finely chopped onion #4 cloves chopped garlic #3 tablespoons dried parsley #½ teaspoon salt #¾ teaspoon dried oregano

name: Valerie's Fruit Dip
description: Spear your favorite fruit on a toothpick and dip it! It will taste fabulous with this creamy vanilla dip!
ingredients: 1 (3.4 ounce) package instant vanilla pudding mix #1 (8 ounce) container frozen whipped topping, thawed #1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, softened #1 cup confectioners' sugar #1 cup whole milk

name: Bonnie's Fruit Dip
description: This is a fruit dip used at all our family get togethers and enjoyed by all.
ingredients: 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, softened #½ cup sour cream, for topping #1 cup whipped cream #¼ cup brown sugar #¼ cup white sugar #1 tablespoon maple syrup #1 teaspoon vanilla extract

name: Tina's Fruit Dip
description: I got this recipe from my mother. It's great with about any type of fruit. Strawberries, bananas, apples and grapes are the best.
ingredients: 1 cup brown sugar #½ cup butter #1 cup sour cream #3 teaspoons vanilla extract

name: Carla's Fruit Dip
description: A thick, creamy fruit dip.
ingredients: 1 (8 ounce) container frozen whipped topping, thawed #1 (7 ounce) jar marshmallow creme #1 (3 ounce) package cream cheese

name: Apple Pie Bread
description: A delicious bread that always gets happy faces! Leave the peels on the apples for added taste and color.
ingredients: 3 cups all-purpose flour #1 cup white sugar #4 teaspoons baking powder #1 teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #1 teaspoon ground cloves #1 ½ cups milk #1 egg #2 tablespoons vegetable oil #1 ½ cups diced apples

name: Twice Baked Potatoes
description: This is great as a side dish or as an appetizer. Melted cheese and crumbled bacon are the highlights of the flavorful, creamy filling.
ingredients: 4 large baking potatoes #½ pound bacon #4 tablespoons butter #1 large onion, chopped #½ cup chopped fresh mushrooms #1 teaspoon crushed red pepper #1 teaspoon garlic powder #1 teaspoon ground black pepper #1 teaspoon chopped fresh chives #1 teaspoon salt #1 (8 ounce) container sour cream #1 (8 ounce) package shredded Cheddar cheese #1 teaspoon dry bread crumbs

name: Creamy Peanut Towers
description: These are perfect for potlucks, get togethers, or as snacks for the kids. Everyone loves them! You may want to quadruple the recipe. Use toothpicks to keep the creamy towers from tumbling.
ingredients: 2 slices white bread #2 tablespoons butter #4 tablespoons peanut butter #1 teaspoon white sugar #1 slice whole wheat bread

name: Mississippi Hot Caviar
description: Different, delicious, DIABLO!
ingredients: 3 (15 ounce) cans black-eyed peas #1 cup diced green chili peppers #¾ cup diced onion #¾ cup diced jalapeno chile pepper #¼ cup diced pimento peppers, drained #1 ½ teaspoons minced garlic #1 (16 ounce) bottle Italian-style salad dressing

name: Delicious Raisin Nut Banana Bread
description: Yummy and soft. Use any kind of raisin nut bran cereal but I like the kind with nut covered raisins. Try yogurt covered ones too!
ingredients: 2 cups raisin nut bran cereal #½ cup milk #¼ cup vegetable oil #1 egg, beaten #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #½ cup white sugar #¼ cup brown sugar #3 ½ teaspoons baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #¼ teaspoon salt #1 cup mashed banana

name: Zucchini Apple Bread
description: A variation of the zucchini bread that is fluffy and light, with a touch of sweetness.
ingredients: 4 eggs #1 cup white sugar #1 cup brown sugar #½ cup vegetable oil #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #3 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 ½ teaspoons baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #2 teaspoons ground cinnamon #½ cup chopped walnuts #2 cups peeled, chopped zucchini #1 cup chopped, peeled apple

name: Easy Nacho Dip
description: A quick and easy dip that everyone loves. Doubling the recipe yields enough for a party. It is great with plain chips or nachos. Sliced black olives may be used as an additional topping.
ingredients: 1 (8 ounce) container sour cream #8 ounces chive and onion cream cheese #1 (1 ounce) package taco seasoning mix #1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese #1 cup chopped tomatoes #2 chopped green onions

name: Aloha Coleslaw
description: The very best slaw I ever had...sweet and crunchy! You can also substitute pineapple tidbits or chunks of fresh pineapple, if you wish.
ingredients: 1 medium head green cabbage, rinsed and very thinly sliced #1 large carrot, shredded #1 (15 ounce) can crushed pineapple, drained #1 cup mayonnaise #1 teaspoon salt

name: Texas Coleslaw
description: One of my favorites! Goes great with barbecues and picnics. For a more mild salad, use less green onions.
ingredients: 1 cup mayonnaise #1 tablespoon lime juice #1 tablespoon ground cumin #1 teaspoon cayenne pepper #1 teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon ground black pepper #1 medium head green cabbage, rinsed and very thinly sliced #1 large carrot, shredded #2 green onions, sliced #2 radishes, sliced

name: Blackberry-Lemon Pie
description: Great blackberry pie with a twist (of lemon).
ingredients: 1 recipe pastry for a 9 inch double crust pie #¾ cup brown sugar #1 tablespoon lemon zest #4 cups fresh blackberries, rinsed and drained #1 cup white sugar #½ cup all-purpose flour #1 tablespoon lemon zest #1 tablespoon butter

name: Green Bean and Feta Salad
description: A tasty salad using fresh green beans and feta cheese in a tangy dressing.
ingredients: 1 ½ pounds fresh green beans #1 sweet onion, peeled #2 cloves garlic, chopped #½ cup rice wine vinegar #½ cup apple cider vinegar #⅓ cup canola oil #1 tablespoon white sugar #¾ teaspoon salt # ground black pepper to taste #1 dash hot sauce #1 dash Worcestershire sauce #4 ounces feta cheese, crumbled

name: Double Tomato Bruschetta
description: A delicious and easy appetizer. The balsamic vinegar gives it a little bite. Dried basil can be substituted but it is best with fresh.
ingredients: 6 roma (plum) tomatoes, chopped #½ cup sun-dried tomatoes, packed in oil #3 cloves minced garlic #¼ cup olive oil #2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar #¼ cup fresh basil, stems removed #¼ teaspoon salt #¼ teaspoon ground black pepper #1 French baguette #2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese

name: Veal Oscar
description: Sauteed veal medallions with crab and asparagus, topped with a cheese sauce. You can use a combination of cheeses instead of just cheddar, or even a store bought cheese sauce to save time.
ingredients: 2 tablespoons butter #½ cup milk #1 pound shredded Cheddar cheese #2 pounds veal cutlets #1 cup all-purpose flour for coating #1 tablespoon butter #16 spears fresh asparagus #8 ounces crabmeat

name: Drunken Stuffed Figs
description: This has been a hit at many dinner parties. Figs are stuffed with a creamy, rich mascarpone cheese and cognac mixture, then rolled in toasted hazelnuts. Garnish with whole hazelnuts and mint leaves when serving. If an injector is unavailable, marinate the figs in 1/2 cup cognac for approximately 30 minutes.
ingredients: 24 fresh figs #1 cup cognac #1 cup mascarpone cheese #½ cup confectioners' sugar #1 ½ cups toasted hazelnuts #2 tablespoons chopped fresh mint leaves

name: Yummy Artichoke Dip
description: Mmmmm Mmmm good!!! Generous amounts of Parmesan cheese make this dip a sure crowd pleaser. Serve with corn chips. Substitute chopped jalapeno peppers for the green chiles if you dare.
ingredients: 1 (6.5 ounce) jar marinated artichoke hearts, drained and quartered #1 cup mayonnaise #1 ½ cups grated Parmesan cheese #1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, softened #1 (4 ounce) can chopped green chile peppers

name: Glazed Meatloaf II
description: This meatloaf is great! It's my husband's favorite. The glaze makes it delicious and moist.
ingredients: ½ cup ketchup #⅓ cup brown sugar #1 tablespoon lemon juice #1 teaspoon dry mustard #2 pounds lean ground beef #3 slices bread, shredded #¼ cup diced onion #1 egg, beaten #1 cube beef bouillon, crumbled #3 tablespoons lemon juice

name: Meatloaf Supreme
description: Enjoy! Read the reviews before making.
ingredients: 2 pounds lean ground beef #4 (6 ounce) cans tomato paste #15 ounces dry bread crumbs #4 large eggs eggs #3 tablespoons garlic salt #3 tablespoons seasoning salt

name: Rempel Family Meatloaf
description: Tired of boring old meat loaf? Well give this one a try. My husband won't eat any other meat loaf but mine.
ingredients: 1 ½ pounds lean ground beef #½ cup crushed buttery round crackers #¾ cup shredded Cheddar cheese #1 (1 ounce) package dry onion soup mix #2 eggs, beaten #¼ cup ketchup #2 tablespoons steak sauce

name: Breakfast Burritos de Frank
description: An inspired breakfast treat! A jumble of my favorite foods (eggs, beans, cheese, salsa) make breakfast friendly!
ingredients: 1 (15 ounce) can black beans, drained #2 tablespoons vegetable oil #8 eggs #8 (10 inch) flour tortillas #1 ½ cups shredded Cheddar cheese #1 (16 ounce) jar salsa

name: Ham and Corn Beignets
description: These deep fried fritters are amazing! They may sound a little different, but they are remarkably easy to make and will take you way down South. Serve with cayenne butter (melted butter with some cayenne added), or with cayenne aioli (mayonnaise with fresh garlic and cayenne pepper in it). Try garnishing with thinly sliced green onions. Enjoy!
ingredients: 2 quarts vegetable oil for frying #4 ears fresh corn #4 eggs #¾ cup milk #10 ounces diced cooked ham #1 tablespoon cayenne pepper #½ cup finely diced red onion #1 tablespoon salt #3 cups all-purpose flour #1 tablespoon baking powder

name: Easy Mexican Casserole
description: This Mexican casserole is easy to make and very tasty. I often substitute with ground turkey and low-fat dairy products, and it's still delicious! Serve this casserole with chips, salsa, and green salad.
ingredients: 1 pound lean ground beef #2 cups salsa #1 (16 ounce) can chili beans, drained #3 cups tortilla chips, crushed #2 cups sour cream #1 (2 ounce) can sliced black olives, drained #½ cup chopped green onion #½ cup chopped fresh tomato #2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese

name: Tasty Meat Pie
description: This pie has been in the family for years. It is good, and my kids love it.
ingredients: 1 pound ground beef #1 onion, chopped #1 (10.75 ounce) can condensed vegetable beef soup, undiluted #1 (10.75 ounce) can condensed cream of mushroom soup #3 potatoes, peeled and cubed #4 carrots, sliced #¼ teaspoon salt #⅛ teaspoon black pepper #1 recipe pastry for a 9 inch double crust pie

name: Muffin Morning Makers
description: These breakfast muffin sandwiches are perfecto for a quick breakfast at home. I like to freeze them and pop them in the microwave for a grab and go breakfast. These sandwiches don't need to be made with sausage, they can be made vegetarian, with ham, bacon or any type of meat you enjoy in the mornings.
ingredients: 1 (12 ounce) package English muffins #6 eggs #¼ cup chopped green onion #1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese #2 ½ tablespoons vegetable oil #6 ounces ground breakfast sausage

name: Mexicorn
description: This is a bright, colorful salad that anyone could love.
ingredients: 3 (15 ounce) cans black beans, rinsed and drained #3 (15.25 ounce) cans whole kernel corn, drained #½ red onion, diced #2 green bell peppers, diced #1 (7 ounce) jar roasted red peppers, drained and diced #⅓ cup red wine vinegar #⅓ cup canola oil

name: Hamburger Pie
description: I'm not sure where this recipe came from, but it's been one of my favorites since I was a kid. Now that I'm grown up, I make it for my husband and he loves it, too.
ingredients: 4 potatoes #1 pound lean ground beef #1 onion, chopped #2 (10.75 ounce) cans condensed tomato soup #1 (15 ounce) can green beans, drained #1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese

name: Banana Blast I
description: Fantastic and healthy smoothie for a quick breakfast or an energizing snack...
ingredients: 1 banana #1 pinch ground nutmeg #½ teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup milk #2 cups crushed ice

name: Basic Margarita
description: This is a basic margarita recipe. You can add your favorite fresh fruits to flavor it. Fresh strawberry or mango are good choices. For a little something different, try granulated sugar rims on the glasses instead of margarita salt.
ingredients: 5 fluid ounces tequila #3 fluid ounces triple sec #2 (6 ounce) cans frozen limeade concentrate #4 cups ice cubes # coarse salt

name: Shortcut Shepherd's Pie
description: This isn't the traditional Shepherd's Pie with lamb, but a quick and easy version my family loves.
ingredients: 5 potatoes, peeled and quartered #1 pound lean ground beef #1 (4 ounce) can sliced mushrooms #1 (15 ounce) can mixed vegetables #1 (10.75 ounce) can condensed cream of mushroom soup #1 (10.75 ounce) can condensed cream of celery soup # salt and pepper to taste #3 tablespoons butter

name: Bordeaux Martini
description: A clean, refreshing essence of lemon martini. Invented by Tito Class, owner of Mona's Bistro in Seattle, WA. Their best martini! Submitted by Chris Blake - bartender and friend.
ingredients: 8 fluid ounces citron vodka #2 fluid ounces Lillet blanc #1 lemon

name: Baked Omelet Roll
description: This omelet is so easy and delicious. It bakes in the oven, so there is no watching the stove. My son loves to make it for us.
ingredients: 6 eggs #1 cup milk #½ cup all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon salt #¼ teaspoon ground black pepper #1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese

name: Breakfast Treat
description: This recipe is put together the night before and then baked in the morning.
ingredients: 6 slices bread #1 (8 ounce) package processed cheese slices #1 ½ cups diced cooked ham #¼ cup butter, melted #4 eggs, beaten #¼ teaspoon salt #½ teaspoon ground dry mustard #2 cups milk

name: Champagne Peach Punch
description: I first made this punch for a wedding 25 years ago. I found a recipe for a peach punch but didn't care for it. This is my adaptation that actually tastes good. This is nice with a ring of ice with fruit or edible flowers frozen into it. Garnish with fruit or mint leaves.
ingredients: 3 (11.5 ounce) cans peach nectar #1 (6 ounce) can frozen orange juice concentrate #¼ cup lemon juice #½ cup peach brandy #¼ cup grenadine syrup #1 (32 fluid ounce) bottle carbonated water #3 (750 milliliter) bottles champagne

name: Asiago Toasted Cheese Puffs
description: A rich and tasty appetizer. People will request the recipe EVERY time you make it!
ingredients: 1 cup grated Asiago cheese #1 teaspoon pressed garlic #⅓ cup mayonnaise #1 teaspoon dried oregano #1 teaspoon dried thyme #1 teaspoon dried parsley #1 pinch salt #1 pinch ground black pepper #1 French baguette, thinly sliced

name: Berry Blend Salad
description: This is an excellent salad and uses no added sugar in the dressing! It will yield 8 small or 4 large salads.
ingredients: 2 cups torn romaine lettuce #1 cup torn radicchio #1 cup torn escarole #1 cup torn red leaf lettuce #1 cup snow peas #½ cup sliced fresh strawberries #1 cup diced cooked ham #½ cup diced Muenster cheese #½ cup raspberry vinegar #½ cup canola oil #8 packets artificial sweetener #2 teaspoons Dijon mustard #¼ teaspoon dried oregano #¼ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper

name: Breakfast Cake
description: This simple cake is great with coffee or a nice addition to any brunch.
ingredients: 1 cup white sugar #2 tablespoons shortening #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 cup milk #¼ cup brown sugar #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon

name: Breakfast Pizza I
description: This is a simple yet different breakfast recipe. It is great for company.
ingredients: 1 pound ground breakfast sausage #1 (8 ounce) package refrigerated crescent rolls #1 cup frozen hash brown potatoes, thawed #1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese #5 eggs #¼ cup milk #½ teaspoon salt #⅛ teaspoon ground black pepper #¼ cup grated Parmesan cheese

name: Orange Cream Milkshake
description: Our family loves milkshakes in the summer to cool off. The creamy orange flavor of this shake was a big hit.
ingredients: ½ cup milk #4 scoops vanilla ice cream #3 tablespoons frozen orange juice concentrate, thawed

name: Exotic Fruit Drink
description: This contains three different fruit juices that everyone will love! Use your imagination and come up with different combinations!
ingredients: 1 cup orange juice #1 cup cranberry juice #½ cup lemon juice #1 (32 fluid ounce) bottle carbonated water
